In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 2013 as National Wilderness Month. He highlights the importance of preserving America's wild and scenic places, which provide opportunities for outdoor activities and contribute to the nation's economy. President Obama mentions his administration's efforts to designate wilderness areas and protect rivers, as well as the establishment of new national monuments. He also emphasizes the value of these areas in supporting local businesses and creating jobs. The article calls on Americans to visit and enjoy wilderness areas, learn about their history, and contribute to their protection.